                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16829270" author="thw" created="Mon, 29 Apr 2019 13:38:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A possible solution is to replace the &quot;finish bundle callback&quot; with a &quot;post snapshot callback&quot; and advance the watermark only then. No additional state needs to be part of the snapshot, since the next watermark is certain to follow.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16829310" author="mxm" created="Mon, 29 Apr 2019 14:41:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another solution could be to finish the bundle until no new bundle is started anymore. That should be possible because no new watermarks arrive during the checkpoint.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16832416" author="mxm" created="Fri, 3 May 2019 10:35:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolving, since this is fixed. If we want to do any additional refactoring, we can still do that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
